.RH MOD.RECIPES-SOURCE WIELKANOC-8 D "25 Mar 88" 1989
.RZ "SERNIK WIELANOCNY" "Easter Cheese Cake"
.IH "Serves 12\-16"
.SH		DOUGH
.IG "1\(34 cups" "white flour" "175 g"
.IG "\(34 tsp" "baking powder" "5 ml"
.IG "\(14 tsp" "salt" "1 ml"
.IG "\(14 cup" "butter" "60 ml"
.IG "1" "egg"
.IG "3 Tbsp" "sour cream" "50 ml"
.IG "1/3 cup" "icing sugar" "50 g"
.SH		FILLING
.IG "6" "eggs"
.IG "2\(14 cups" "icing sugar" "300 g"
.IG "1\(12 lbs" "farmers cheese" "700 g"
(or ricotta)
.IG "2/3 cup" "butter," 150 g"
at room temperature
.IG "\(12 tsp" "salt" "2.5 ml"
.IG "1\(12 tsp" "vanilla extract" "7.5 ml"
.IG "2 tsp" "grated lemon rind" "10 ml"
.IG "\(14 cup" "chopped candied citrus peel" "40 g"
.IG "1/3 cup" "raisins" "40 g"
.SH		SPREAD
.IG "\(34 cup" "raspberry or strawberry preserves" "200 ml"
.SK 1
Preheat oven to
.TE 325 160 .
For dough, combine flour, baking powder, and salt in a bowl.  Cut in butter.
.SK 2
Beat egg into sour cream.  Stir into flour mixture.  Stir in sugar.  Knead
dough until well mixed and smooth.
.SK 3
Roll dough on a floured surface into a rectangle.  Line a casserole or
rectangular cake pan with dough, and bring dough part way up sides.
.SK 4
For filling, beat eggs at high speed until thickened.  Slowly beat in sugar,
beating until mixture piles softly.
.SK 5
Press cheese through a sieve.  Beat cheese with butter, salt, vanilla
extract, and lemon peel.
.SK 6
Fold eggs into cheese mixture.  Stir in orange peel and raisins.
.SK 7
Spread preserves over bottom of prepared crust in pan.
.SK 8
Turn cheese mixture into pan.
.SK 9
Bake at
.TE 325 160
for 45 minutes to 1 hour, or until knife inserted near
center comes out clean.
.SK 10
Cool completely before cutting.
.SH RATING
.I Difficulty:
medium.
.I Time:
1 hour preparation, 1 hour cooking.
.I Precision:
Measure the ingredients.
.WR
Original recipe passed down through the generations and translated from
Polish into English by
Edward Chrzanowski
MFCF, University of Waterloo, Waterloo, Ontario, Canada
echrzanowski@watmath.waterloo.edu  or {decvax,att,utzoo}!watmath!echrzanowski
